Song 13
1. Darkness and sorrows may surround me;
   Troubles may try to overcome me;
   Not one small glimmer of light I may see;
   Still I trust in my God for He has said:

   \tIn times of trouble do thou call upon me - 2
   \tIf you will surely believe you will see,
   \tThat all your troubles soon will have to flee.

2. Satan may try to come and shake me;
   He may try his best to put me to shame.
   With His glamour he may try to deceive me;
   Still I trust in my God for He has said : - In times of...
